examples.en: The island's birds are quite tame.
This was the island's first colonial settlement.
Many people enjoy diving on the island's coral reefs.
Fire has caused extensive damage to the island's forests.
...the pellucid waters that lap upon that island's beaches...
Tourism has had far-reaching effects on the island's culture.
We sailed past the island's rather dark and forbidding cliffs.
The cool waters of the North Atlantic bathe the island's shores.
Each year the sea continues to encroach upon the island's beaches.
A lone lighthouse beacons the entrance to the island's only harbor.
At one time pelagic whaling was the cornerstone of the island's economy.
Scientists are concerned about the rapid disappearance of the island's coral reefs.
Only animals with strong constitutions are able to survive the island's harsh winters.
The beautiful beaches are the island's main attraction (=most popular place, activity etc).
The island's population initially numbered 180, but there was a gradual decline until only 40 people were left.
